<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="372" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[125,760,1803,2100]" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">
<emphasis box="[155,269,1871,1895]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Etymology</emphasis>
: A combination of 
<collectingCountry box="[476,541,1874,1896]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Persia</collectingCountry>
and scape, referring to the similarity with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levy" authorityYear="1996" box="[354,475,1905,1929]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Agelescape" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[354,475,1905,1929]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Agelescape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="372" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[125,760,1803,2100]" lastBlockId="4.[828,1464,1239,2100]" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">
<emphasis box="[155,263,1941,1964]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2020" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2020" box="[277,394,1941,1964]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Persiscape" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[277,394,1941,1964]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Persiscape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[401,474,1943,1963]" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levy" authorityYear="1996" box="[605,726,1939,1963]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Agelescape" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[605,726,1939,1963]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Agelescape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the number of the teeth on the promargin of the chelicera, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
the new genus and 
<quantity box="[356,422,2010,2032]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.89" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="7.62" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" unit="in" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3â€“4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levy" authorityYear="1996" box="[422,543,2007,2031]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Agelescape" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[422,543,2007,2031]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Agelescape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Males of this genus differ from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levy" authorityYear="1996" box="[338,459,2041,2065]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Agelescape" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[338,459,2041,2065]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Agelescape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a complex embolus with a thumb-like base, a short embolus proper (stick- like portion) (not longer than tegular apophysis), an embolar lamellar process (Pe), conductor twisted around its axis with a thumb-like base and rounded tip (
<taxonomicName box="[1211,1327,1305,1328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" rank="variety" variety="embolus">
<emphasis box="[1211,1223,1305,1328]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">v</emphasis>
. embolus
</taxonomicName>
unmodified, filamentous, longer than tegular apophysis, conductor gradually tapering, untwisted, with a sharp tip) and by the shape of the tegular apophysis in lateral view: apophysis straight, longer than wide, with parallel lateral margins and an abrupt tip (
<taxonomicName box="[874,1008,1473,1496]" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" rank="variety" variety="apophysis">
<emphasis box="[874,890,1473,1496]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">v.</emphasis>
apophysis
</taxonomicName>
with diverging margins and rounded tip) (
<figureCitation box="[832,906,1508,1530]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[125,156,1762,1781]" captionTargetBox="[140,1447,151,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[140,1447,151,1739]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 6: SEM micrographs of male palps. A Persiscape gideoni, bulb, ventral view; B P. ecbatana sp. n., bulb, ventral view; C P. levyi, bulb, ventral view; D Agelescape cf. livida, from Israel, bulb, ventral view; E P. ecbatana sp. n., bulb, retrolateral view; F Gorbiscape gorbachevi sp. n., bulb, ventral view; G Agelescape cf. livida, from Israel, whole palp with removed bulb; H same, bulb, anterior view; I Persiscape gideoni, bulb, anterior view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm, if not otherwise indicated. Abbreviations: Be = base of embolus, Cb = base of conductor, Co = conductor, Em = embolus, Pe = embolar process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3925229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3925229/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
Aâ€“C, E, I, 7Bâ€“C, 9Aâ€“F, 10Aâ€“F, 11Aâ€“F). Females of the two genera differ by the presence of wide and straight copulatory ducts and the receptacles subdivided into 2â€“3 globular chambers in the new genus (
<emphasis box="[1230,1245,1607,1630]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">v.</emphasis>
tube-like, bent, true copulatory ducts and an undivided receptacle in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levy" authorityYear="1996" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Agelescape" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Agelescape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[926,1019,1675,1697]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[125,156,1465,1484]" captionTargetBox="[125,1450,151,1425]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[125,1463,151,1426]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 12: Epigynes, different specimens showing variation.A Persiscape levyi, ventral view;B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view;D same, dorsal view; E same, ventral view; F same, posterior view; G same, dorsal view; H P. gideoni, ventral view; I, D same, posterior views; K, L same, dorsal views; M P. caucasica, ventral view; N same, posterior view; O same, dorsal view. Eâ€“G, Hâ€“I, Lâ€“O after Guseinov, Marusik &amp; Koponen (2005). Scale bars = 0.2 mm, unless otherwise indicated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3925241" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3925241/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Figs. 12</figureCitation>
Aâ€“O). 
<taxonomicName authority="Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2020" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2020" box="[1089,1206,1674,1697]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Persiscape" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[1089,1206,1674,1697]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Persiscape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1211,1282,1677,1697]" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2020" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2020" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Asiascape" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Asiascape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[910,984,1710,1730]" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the presence of an embolar process (Pe) (
<taxonomicName box="[837,939,1742,1765]" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" rank="variety" variety="absent">
<emphasis box="[837,852,1742,1765]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">v.</emphasis>
absent
</taxonomicName>
) and globular receptacles subdivided into 2â€“3 chambers (
<taxonomicName box="[945,1045,1775,1798]" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" rank="variety" variety="tubular">
<emphasis box="[945,961,1775,1798]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">v.</emphasis>
tubular
</taxonomicName>
receptacles).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="373" pageId="4" pageNumber="372" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[828,1464,1239,2100]" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">
<emphasis box="[858,984,1809,1832]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Description</emphasis>
: Total length: male 5.30â€“8.55, female 6.78â€“ 11.20. Carapace length: male 2.50â€“4.25, female 2.30â€“4.30, width: male 1.60â€“3.00, female 1.90â€“3.00. Chelicera with 2 prolateral and 3 retrolateral teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[828,1464,1239,2100]" lastBlockId="5.[125,760,877,1876]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="373" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">
Carapace and abdomen with distinct pattern (
<figureCitation box="[1329,1403,1944,1966]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[125,156,1514,1533]" captionTargetBox="[138,1457,160,1491]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[125,1463,151,1508]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1: A Persiscape caspica sp. n., â™€ habitus; B same, â™‚ habitus; C Persilena sengleti sp. n., â™€ habitus; D Asiascape parthica sp. n., â™‚ habitus; E Gorbiscape gorbachevi sp. n., â™‚ habitus; F same, â™€ habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3925219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3925219/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="372">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
Aâ€“B, 2Aâ€“C, 3Câ€“D). Yellowish to reddish-brown, with two wide submarginal bands and a thin gray margin. Sternum grayish with yellow median stripe. Legs usually the same color as carapace, with obscure annulations in some species. Abdomen dark gray with a pattern of lighter spots dorsally, ventrally light gray. Spinnerets yellowish.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3925225" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3925225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3925225/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="373" startId="5.[125,156,721,740]" targetBox="[148,733,152,698]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[125,760,717,813]" pageId="5" pageNumber="373">
